00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:05,000
The Great Ancient Detective's Bizarre Investigation
[Title: The Great Ancient Detective's Bizarre Investigation]

3
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:24,400
また悪い夢を見た。
Another bad dream.

4
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:38,200
陰惨な現場が日常の探偵という職業には、
悪夢は付き物と言ってもいいでしょう。
Perhaps nightmares are the penalty a detective pays
for being in a gruesome business.

5
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:43,100
だが、気にしている場合ではない。
So be it. It's not about to stop.

6
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:49,000
彼女のもとに、また新たな事件が
舞い込んできているからだ。
Not when there are new cases to be solved.

7
00:02:57,650 --> 00:02:59,500
UNHAPPY? 悩める人の子よ
UNHAPPY? Children of man full of worries

8
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,350
UNLUCKY? 人成らざる者も
UNLUCKY? Those who are not yet men

9
00:03:01,350 --> 00:03:03,200
BE HAPPY! 弛まず目指せよ
BE HAPPY! Aim without an ounce of slack,

10
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,100
UNDEAD 生きているんだし
UNDEAD You're alive, you know!

11
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:08,800
目を逸らした過去も 退屈な未来も
Even for the past you averted your gaze from
And your future with nothing fun to do

12
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,700
カウンセリング やれやれ
counseling, what a bummer

13
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:13,500
古今東西 ピースピース
Throughout all ages and places, peace peace!

14
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:16,000
UNDEAD
Lyrics, Music: Ayase
[Song: UNDEAD / Lyrics, Music: Ayase]

15
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,000
ねえ何だかどうして
Hey, why do I kinda get that feeling

16
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,750
戦ってるようなそんな気がするの
that I'm fighting who-knows-what?

17
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:29,600
触れられない 触れたくもない
Can't touch, don't want to touch

18
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,450
過去の自分自分自分自分と
My past self self self self

19
00:03:31,450 --> 00:03:33,300
もうとっくに死んでる
They've already died

20
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:35,150
透明な亡霊と対決
I'm confronting see-through ghosts

21
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:37,300
幼気で痛い記憶の奥
from deep in painful memories of my own tender youth

22
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,200
残念？ もう居ないのに
Too bad? Even though they're already gone

23
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:41,100
あれ？ そっちが良い？ アイロニーね
Huh? Prefer that? Ironic, right?

24
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:44,200
透かされているのは現在の自分？
Is your current self see-through?

25
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,100
ナンセンス 消えないレッテル
Nonsense, can't get rid of the label

26
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,000
Yes! 要はコンプレックス
Yes! Basically it's a complex,

27
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,300
取り憑かれているみたい
Like something’s got its hold on you

28
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:53,200
巻き付いたまま
I'm still all wrapped up

29
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,050
まだ離れない
they won't let me go—

30
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:56,800
在りし日の自分
in my past selves,

31
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,700
UNDEAD

32
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,600
死んじゃいない お前とお前の連鎖
They're, not, dead!
The chain linking you and you together!

33
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:04,300
生きていることとは変わり続けることだ
To be alive is to continue to change

34
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:08,100
不幸に甘んじて 満足するなよ
Don't go finding satisfaction
in resigning yourself to your discontentment

35
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:11,850
幸せになろうとしないなんて卑怯だ
The fact that you refuse to even try to be happy, you coward!

36
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:13,750
この世この世は 奇怪奇怪ファンタジー
This world, the present world we live in
is one devilishly odd fantasy

37
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:17,350
次は鬼が出るか蛇が出るか
Who knows what we'll come across next, a devil or a snake?

38
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:21,100
出会って遭ってやっと始まる物語
Our story finally starts to happen after chance
meetings and unfortunate encounters

39
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:24,850
さあ人か化物か 閑話休題 ピースピース
So, will it be a human or monster?
Now, back to the topic that's at hand, peace peace!

40
00:04:24,850 --> 00:04:26,150
Past & Future

41
00:04:26,150 --> 00:04:28,500
can't change the Past

42
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,400
Past & Future

43
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,250
run for the Future

44
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:34,100
カットイン
(Ka-ka!) Cu-cu-cut in!

45
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,950
何だかどうして
Why does it feel like

46
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:37,850
未来になんぞ
there's no hope

47
00:04:37,850 --> 00:04:41,550
何の希望もない期待出来ない
to be had for the future
and nothing to expect

48
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:43,350
ような気がして
I kinda get that feeling

49
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:45,150
もう随分生きている
I've been living long enough.

50
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:48,900
既視感とテンプレで食傷
Fed up with deja-vu and the same stuff as always

51
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:52,550
素敵な出来事の気配もない
with no sign of anything wonderful coming up.

52
00:04:52,550 --> 00:04:53,950
残念
Too bad…

53
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:55,750
積んだ経験の因果
Karma from accumulating experiences

54
00:04:55,750 --> 00:04:59,500
形骸化された神話と退屈な進化
with myths reduced to shells of formality and stale evolution

55
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:00,000
要は刺激が欲しいんだ
The point, all I want is stimulation

56
00:05:00,048 --> 00:05:01,348
同じ味がする
Everything tastes the same

57
00:05:01,348 --> 00:05:02,848
アンデッド！
Undead!

58
